    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "If I set the deadline for 2 seconds and make a call to a host I know doesn't resolve; currently my client blocks for a very very very long time. More than a couple minutes. I was convinced that it would hang forever so I let it run overnight. At some point it bailed. But it's certainly not 2 seconds.\nThis is C++ on OSX and if I pause with a debugger I see that there are two threads. the thread where my code makes the call, and then a thread where grpc is blocking on getaddrinfo.\n\nI just realized that I have timestamps on my logging output so when I get another look I'll note the actual time.\n\nHow can figure out what's wrong here?\n"
  },
