    "created_at": "2016-10-27T07:17:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-27T07:17:25Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "If I first use `channel->WaitForConnected()` with my timeout it works as expected and regardless of that, attempting to make a call will sit and block for the aforementioned amount of time.\nSo checking for the connection first will prevent the client from locking up at least during initialization. \nI'd like to find out if I'm simply doing something incorrectly though that prevents this mechanism from having the desired effect for a regular call.\nThere are cases where a connection might have worked but won't be possible for a period of time. I need to be able to handle these situations.\n"
