    "created_at": "2016-10-27T12:42:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-27T12:42:29Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "_head smack_\n\nAfter way too much time (doing other stuff thankfully) I finally realized that the timeout for some calls was previously using milliseconds for timeouts (how the previous RPC library interpreted, and in an effort to avoid having to start using std::chrono::duration everywhere, I just converted the int provided into seconds. :/\n~35 min turns out to be 33.3333 minutes or so when you set the deadline to be 2000 seconds. Everybody has to use std::chrono::duration now instead and so problem solved. Sorry to waste your time!\n"
